        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>*[In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis <persName key="#Emperor/king #Imperial/royal_diploma #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium"
                            ref="#people/127">HENRICUS</persName> Dei gratia quartus Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/3556">HERIMANNO</persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbati</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Islands #Churches #Tolls #Ports #Curtes #Hospitals #Landed_possessions #Imperial/royal_diploma #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Immunity"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">sancti Benedicti iuxta Padum</orgName>
                        suisque]* successoribus regulariter in perpetuum substituendis. Sane
                        credimus nos in huius vitae cursu feliciter imperare, si studuerimus circa
                        Dei aecclesias opera pietatis exercere et ipsas earumque bona imperiali
                        potentia a Deo nobis concessa conservare atque defendere. Quapropter omnibus
                        Christi nostrisque fidelibus tam futuris quam presentibus notum fieri
                        volumus qualiter nos omnipotentis Dei causa et ob regni nostri stabilitatem
                        et anime nostrae nostrorumque parentum perpetuam salutem, devota et
                        exaudibili petitione fratrum sancti Benedicti quorum diligimus et habeamus,
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> sancti Benedicti situm inter
                        Padum et Larionem, et <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> modo in eodem loco sunt
                        vel post futuri per regularem conversationem et omnia eius bona mobilia et
                        immobilia scilicet <placeName key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#places/2400"
                                ><rs key="#Islands">insulam</rs> sancti Benedicti</placeName> cum
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2058"><rs
                                key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> sancti Floriani</orgName> et omnibus
                        ad eandem pertinentibus. Insula etiam quae vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#places/2403">Gurgo</placeName>, cum
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2059">aecclesia eiusdem
                            insule</orgName> et pertinentiis suis. <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/2931">Casale Barbatum</placeName> cum ecclesia sancte
                        Mariae et sancti Laurentii, earnmque pertinentiis. <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/2476">Septingenti</placeName> cum aecclesia
                            <orgName key="#Churches #Ports" ref="#juridical_persons/2064">sancti
                            Michaelis</orgName>, eiusque pertinentiis et cum <rs key="#Tolls #Ports"
                            >de transitu navium</rs>. Decimam partem <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/2050"><rs key="#Curtes">curtis</rs> quae vocatur
                                <placeName key="#Curtes #Churches" ref="#places/482"
                                >Burbassium</placeName></geogName>, cum aecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2003">sancti Iohannis</orgName>
                        suisque pertinentiis. Locum qui vocatur <placeName ref="#places/624"
                            >Nucetula</placeName>. <orgName key="#Hospitals"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2077"><rs key="#Hospitals">Domum hospitalis</rs>
                            apud <placeName key="#Hospitals" ref="#places/275"
                            >Mantuam</placeName></orgName>, cum pertinentiis suis. Ecclesiam
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2067">sancti
                            Valentini</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#places/2932">Maringo</placeName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> ab eadem detentis. Ecclesias
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2066">sancti
                            Viti</orgName> et <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2004"
                            >sancti Iusti</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2475"
                            >Medula</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis et terras quas predictum
                        monasterium ibi possidet. Ecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2074">sancti Michaelis</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/2936">Cotorlione</placeName> cum
                        pertinentiis suis. Ecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2068">sancti Benedicti</orgName> apud <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/77">Ficariolum</placeName>, et Ä™cclesiam
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2098">sancte
                            Agathae</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/80"
                            >Ferariam</placeName>, cum ambarum pertinentiis. Monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/2075">sancti
                            Cypriani</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/914"
                            >Venetiam</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis. Ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2076">sancte Helenae</orgName>
                        apud <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2938">Tassariam</placeName> cum
                        pertinentiis suis. <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2969"
                            >Concam</placeName> cum ecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2099">sancti Leonardi</orgName> et omnibus
                        appenditiis suis. Locum qui dicitur <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/2970">Foculare</placeName> cum aecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#juridical_persons/2400">sancti
                            Nicholai</orgName>, et omnibus <rs key="#Decima">decimis</rs> eiusdem
                        loci. Ecclesias <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2006"
                            >sancti Benedicti</orgName> et <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2080">sanctae Mariae</orgName> apud <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/2414">Gunzagam</placeName> cum
                        omnibus decimis eiusdem loci, caeterisque earum pertinentiis. <placeName
                            ref="#places/2929">Caput vici</placeName>. <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/362">Villulam</placeName> cum
                        aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2079">sanctae
                            Mariae</orgName>, et cum omnibus decimis et pertinentiis suis,
                            <placeName key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/2417"
                            >Custellum</placeName> cum aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2054">sancti Bartholomei</orgName> et omnibus
                        decimis eiusdem loci, <placeName key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/2930"
                            >Gabianam</placeName> cum ecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2060">sancti Andreae</orgName>, et omnibus
                        decimis eiusdem loci. Ecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2061">sancti Venerii</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Castle" ref="#places/2900">Marceneta</placeName>, cum
                        medietate eiusdem <rs key="#Castle">castri</rs> et pertinentiis suis.
                        Ecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2073">sancti
                            Michaelis</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2935"
                            >Telliore</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis. Ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2090">sancti
                            Bartholomei</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/4"
                            >Luca</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis. <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2087">Sanctum Martinum</orgName> in <placeName
                            ref="#places/2940">Colle</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis. Ecclesiam
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2071">sancti
                            Leonardi</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches #Dioecesis"
                            ref="#places/53">Parmam</placeName>, et omnia quae predictum monasterium
                        in eodem <rs key="#Dioecesis">episcopatu</rs> detinet. Ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2081">sancti Syxti</orgName> de
                            <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/361">Lecto Paludano</placeName>
                        et aecclesias <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2069">sanctae
                            Mariae</orgName> et <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/74"
                            >sancti Johannis</orgName> in episcopatu <placeName
                            key="#Dioecesis #Churches" ref="#places/7">Bononiensi</placeName> cum
                        pertinentiis suis. Decimas de <placeName key="#Decima" ref="#places/2972"
                            >Roncis Gunthardi</placeName>. Terras quas predictum monasterium detinet
                        in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2410"
                            >Monticulo</placeName> et in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#places/2971">Birupto</placeName>. Abbatiam <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/2413">sanctae Marie de
                            Strata</orgName>, quam prefatus venerabiliis abbas Herimannus monasterio
                        sancti Benedicti acquisivit et univit; caeteraque omnia quae predictum
                        monasterium nunc tenet vel in futuro acquisierit, per hanc <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">mundiburdialem
                            paginam</rs> in tutelam nostre defensionis ponimus, precipientes et
                        presenti scripto confirmantes ut nulla clericalis vel laicalis persona
                        aliquam dominationem aut ullum penitus <rs>prelationis ius</rs> in prefato
                        monasterio sancti Benedicti praeter <rs key="#Popes">Romanum pontificem</rs>
                        et imperatorem in perpetuum requirat vel habeat. <rs key="#Immunity"
                            >Statuimus etiam ut nullius unquam persone ingenium vel privilegium
                            contra presentem prefati loci auctoritatem et libertatem valeat, sed
                            idem locus nunc et semper in perpetua libertate permaneat</rs>. Si quis
                        igitur archiepiscopus, episcopus, dux, comes, vel alia quelibet persona
                        cuiuscumque condicionis sit, huius nostre paginam libertatis violare in
                        aliquo presumpserit, <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras auri boni</rs>
                        compositurus, banno nostro subiacebit, dimidietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >camerÄ™ nostrÄ™</rs>, dimidietatem prefate aecclesiÄ™. Ut autem hec carta
                        ab omnibus firma et inviolabilis permaneat, nostri eam sigilli impressione
                        iussimus insigniri, ita tamen nemini legali iudicio hec omnia superius
                        pretaxata a nobis aliter diffimantur. Signum Heynrici quarti Romanorum
                        imperatoris invictissimi. <persName>Philippus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> recognovi vice
                            <persName>Adelberti</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2968">Magontini</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">Archicancellarii</rs>. Data <placeName
                            ref="#places/83">Aquisgrani</placeName> Anno dominice Incarnationis
                        M.C.XXIII. Indictione .XIII. Kalendas decembris. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
